name: portCode
description: The code for the U.S. port where the enclosed transaction(s) are to be ‘processed’.

name: filerCode
description: Filer’s identification code (as assigned by CBP).

name: appCode
description: A code that identifies the type of transaction data within the block.

name: filler2
description: Space fill. Number of input images (i.e., records) submitted in the block. The count does not include the B-Record or the Y-Record. Space fill.

name: officeCode
description: A code agreed upon by the Filer and CBP representing a specific Filer ‘office’ (or sub-location). Space fill if not used.
